# Copy to .env. EXPO_PUBLIC_* is inlined at bundle time — restart Expo (`npx expo start -c`) after changes.
#
# When you change Wi‑Fi, set your Mac's LAN IP so Expo Go can reach Metro (avoids request timed out):
#   ipconfig getifaddr en0
#   REACT_NATIVE_PACKAGER_HOSTNAME=<that IP>
#
# FinanceApp.API ports (see Properties/launchSettings.json):
#   • `http` profile   → http://127.0.0.1:5022  (default; binds localhost only)
#   • `Mobile` profile → http://0.0.0.0:5279   (LAN + simulator; use when testing a physical device)
#
# Port 5279 is also used by FinanceApp.Web (MVC). Do NOT point mobile at Web — you need FinanceApp.API
# or all /api/auth/... calls fail (404 / network errors).
#
# iOS Simulator (on Mac — use loopback + API port):
#   dotnet run --project FinanceApp.API --launch-profile http
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:5022
#
# Physical device (same Wi‑Fi; run API with Mobile profile so it listens on LAN):
#   dotnet run --project FinanceApp.API --launch-profile Mobile
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://YOUR_MAC_LAN_IP:5279
#
# Android Emulator:
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://10.0.2.2:5022
#
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:5022
